raw_data.name: Suffolk Punch Brewing - Birkdale Village
raw_data.full_address: 16912 Birkdale Commons Pkwy, Huntersville, NC 28078, United States

reviews_data.review_text: Great time here tonight. Chelsea and Celene were top notch. Quality beer
Celene and Chelsea provided excellent service! So excited to come back because of them.

Authentic tasting Italian flat breads, bread/cheese/ Fruit/ pickle boards. Food service. Walk up service available as well.  Roof top, indoor and outdoor seating.  Very good. Great service and DOG FRIENDLY OUTSIDE.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Christine,
     Thank you for the wonderful feedback! We are so happy to finally be open. We look forward to seeing you more in the future!

reviews_data.review_text: Such a fun vibe and cool restaurant. The outdoor patio is awesome, the food is so good, and I can’t wait for the rooftop to be open. All of the workers were so nice. I’ll definitely be back!!
This place is fantastic. The service and food was incredible. If you left a bad review then you’re looking for problems. 10/10 will come back.

Maybe it’s the first week cobwebs or the rainy night yucks, but we walked in tonight and couldn’t find the traditional hostess stand so we saw a waiter, asked if we could sit anywhere, and sat outside first floor. Scanned the QR code and saw an EXTREMELY limited menu. I assumed it would be limited but it’s even more limited than what’s online for the other locations. The mocktails aren’t on the QR code menu, but I see they have printed menus with the mocktails based on the photos uploaded here by others, so I’m confused. We never had anyone come to our table which is fine, I would have just ordered from the QR code but it seems like the QR code menu is not up to date. We will try again once they get things worked out or only sit inside.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for stopping by and sharing your experience during our opening week. We appreciate your patience as we work through a few early adjustments.

We’ve since updated our QR code menus to make our mocktails easier to find and to help ensure everything is clearer for guests. That evening also came with an unexpected change to our patio setup, and we’re taking steps to ensure a more seamless experience moving forward.

We truly appreciate the feedback and would love the chance to provide you with a better experience. Please feel free to reach out or let us know the next time you plan to visit!

reviews_data.review_text: Great experience, the whole experience was 10/10

There on Saturday for opening.  Filled with happy patrons and excited servers trying to make it all come together.  And it did.  Great beers and cocktails.  Limited menu but was tasty and not expensive.  Fun indoors and out!  Welcome to my neighborhood.

Draft beers for him, draft prosecco for her, lemonade for them.
Welcome to the hood, Suffolk Punch.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Anton,

Thank you for stopping in once we opened! We hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Opening Night! A long time coming! Have watched and waited…well worth the Wait! Atmosphere is fantastic. Excellent outdoor seating with overhead heaters. Sit at the table and scan QR for ordering. Quite easy. Overall 💯 great experience. Look forward to coming back!
Everyone - this is not a drill! It’s open and amazing! Don’t sleep on it. Friendly staff, perfect location. Lots of seating!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Melissa, 

Thanks so much!! Glad you’re loving the overall vibe! We hope the wait was worth it, because we’re here to stay 😎🙌

- Management
